    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-04-20T02:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-04-20T02:30:00-05:00" n="264"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d264">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">501.<gloss target="#t_BC1">BC</gloss>/4–2048:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Pakistan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Alling</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Karachi</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-04-20T13:00:00+05:30"
                            >April 20, 1948—1 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>230. Saw Prime Minister today and handed him copy draft resolution<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d264fn1">Resolution of April 21 (<gloss target="#t_S1"
                        >S/</gloss>726). See telegram 236, April 17, <ref target="#pg_334">p.
                            334</ref>.</note> Kashmir. I explained some of points in <gloss
                        target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 148, April 17,<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d264fn2">Same as telegram 236 to India, <ref target="#pg_334">p.
                            334</ref>.</note> and told him in my opinion resolution offered all
                    necessary guarantees protect <gloss target="#t_GOP1">GOP</gloss> position and
                    afford fair honest plebiscite. I said if I had responsibility for Pakistan, I
                    would immediately inform UN resolution was acceptable and that <gloss
                        target="#t_GOP1">GOP</gloss> would cooperate fully with <gloss
                        target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> Commission. Prime Minister made no commitments
                    and I judged he had received no instructions from Jinnah who is still <gloss
                        target="#t_NWFP1">NWFP</gloss>. I gathered, however, that Prime Minister’s
                    attitude was much more favorable than it was when I last talked with him April
                    17. He still objected idea troops remaining Kashmir and speculated whether
                        <gloss target="#t_GOP1">GOP</gloss> would be able under such conditions
                    induce Azad forces lay down arms.</p>
                <p>Sent Department 230, which please repeat London if desired. Delhi informed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Alling</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
